{"questionId":"22158788","questionHtml":"<p>Determine the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>finding the number of ways to assign the students with the two students apart</p>\n<p>number of ways to assign two students <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mmultiscripts><mi>C</mi><mn>1</mn><mrow></mrow><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mn>2</mn></mmultiscripts></math> (seen anywhere)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>number of ways to assign others <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mmultiscripts><mi>C</mi><mn>2</mn><mrow></mrow><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mmultiscripts></math> to have one group of 3 (seen anywhere)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>number of ways&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mmultiscripts><mi>C</mi><mn>1</mn><mrow></mrow><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mn>2</mn></mmultiscripts><mo>×</mo><mmultiscripts><mi>C</mi><mn>2</mn><mrow></mrow><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mmultiscripts></math></p>\n<p>attempt to set up an equation involving either half of their answer to part (a) and their number of ways or their answer to part (a) is twice their number of ways&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mmultiscripts><mi>C</mi><mn>3</mn><mrow></mrow><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mi>n</mi></mmultiscripts><mo>=</mo><mmultiscripts><mi>C</mi><mn>1</mn><mrow></mrow><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mn>2</mn></mmultiscripts><mo>×</mo><mmultiscripts><mi>C</mi><mn>2</mn><mrow></mrow><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mmultiscripts></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mmultiscripts><mi>C</mi><mn>3</mn><mrow></mrow><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mi>n</mi></mmultiscripts><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mmultiscripts><mi>C</mi><mn>1</mn><mrow></mrow><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mn>2</mn></mmultiscripts><mo>×</mo><mmultiscripts><mi>C</mi><mn>2</mn><mrow></mrow><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mmultiscripts></math></p>\n<p>valid attempt to eliminate all factorials from their equation&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mrow><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;or equivalent with no factorials</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>12</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>finding the number of ways to assign the students with the two students together</p>\n<p>number of ways to assign two students and one other to the first group <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mmultiscripts><mi>C</mi><mn>1</mn><mrow></mrow><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mmultiscripts></math>&nbsp;(seen anywhere)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>number of ways to assign three other students the first group <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mmultiscripts><mi>C</mi><mn>3</mn><mrow></mrow><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mmultiscripts></math> (seen anywhere)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>number of ways&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mmultiscripts><mi>C</mi><mn>1</mn><mrow></mrow><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mmultiscripts><mo>+</mo><mmultiscripts><mi>C</mi><mn>3</mn><mrow></mrow><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mmultiscripts></math></p>\n<p>attempt to set up an equation involving either half of their answer to part (a) and their number of ways or their answer to part (a) is twice their number of ways&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mmultiscripts><mi>C</mi><mn>3</mn><mrow></mrow><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mi>n</mi></mmultiscripts><mo>=</mo><mmultiscripts><mi>C</mi><mn>1</mn><mrow></mrow><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mmultiscripts><mo>+</mo><mmultiscripts><mi>C</mi><mn>3</mn><mrow></mrow><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mmultiscripts></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mmultiscripts><mi>C</mi><mn>3</mn><mrow></mrow><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mi>n</mi></mmultiscripts><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mmultiscripts><mi>C</mi><mn>1</mn><mrow></mrow><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mmultiscripts><mo>+</mo><mmultiscripts><mi>C</mi><mn>3</mn><mrow></mrow><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mmultiscripts></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>valid attempt to eliminate all factorials from their equation&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mrow><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>13</mn><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>36</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>9</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Do not award the final <em><strong>A1</strong></em> if additional values of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math> are given.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[6 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22158788","referenceCode":"24M.1.AHL.TZ2.9b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Determine the value of n.","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 6]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.10—Perms and combs, binomial with negative and fractional indices"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}